# Team Task Manager (Flask App)

A simple web-based Task Management system built using Flask. It allows users to create, view, update, and manage tasks efficiently.

## Project Structure

app.py → Main Flask application entry point  
config.py → Configuration settings (DB, secrets, etc.)  
database.py → Database connection and helper functions  
schema.sql → Database schema (tables setup)  
templates/ → HTML templates (Flask Jinja2)  
static/ → CSS, JS, images  
venv/ → Virtual environment (NOT for deployment)  
requirements.txt → Python dependencies (must be created)

## Features

- Create new tasks  
- View all tasks  
- Update task status  
- Delete tasks  
- Database integration (SQLite/PostgreSQL depending on config)

## Setup

git clone <your-repo-url>  
cd team-task-manager  

python -m venv venv  

Windows:  
venv\Scripts\activate  

Mac/Linux:  
source venv/bin/activate  

pip install -r requirements.txt  

## Database Setup

python database.py  

## Run Project

python app.py  

Open: http://127.0.0.1:5000/

## Notes

- Do NOT upload venv/  
- Use requirements.txt for dependencies  
- Use environment variables for sensitive data  
- Works on Railway / Render / AWS

## Tech Stack

Python, Flask, HTML, CSS, SQL

